Hyperparameters in ML models are external configuration settings that are not learned from the data but are set prior to the training process. They influence the overall behaviour of the model and affect its performance. Hyperparameters can be optimised using different techniques. Among the studies included in this review, only a very few [W4310275051, W4317600379, W2898812155, W3118385223] conducted hyperparameter tuning. The grid search technique was applied in two of these studies [W4310275051, W4317600379] while the randomised search technique was applied in another one [W2898812155]. (There are not enough details regarding the hyperparameter tuning process in [W3118385223].) Table 3 presents the details of the hyperparameter tuning conducted by past studies. It shows the various hyperparameters tuned with different values and techniques.

